===Etymology===
From Latin [[fasciculus]], a diminutive of [[fascis]] ‘bundle’.  [[Category:Latin derivations]]

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˈfæsɪkəl/}}
*{{audio|en-us-fascicle.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[bundle]] or [[cluster]].
# {{anatomy}}: A bundle of [[skeletal]] [[muscle]] [[fiber]]s surrounded by [[connective tissue]].
# {{botany}}: A [[cluster]] of [[flowers]] or [[leaves]], such as the bundles of the thin leaves (or needles) of [[pine]]s.
# {{botany}}: A [[discrete]] bundle of [[vascular]] [[tissue]].
# A discrete [[section]] of a book [[issue]]d or published separately.

